resulting scheme is shown to be stable at density jumps and free
boundaries, in contrast to an earlier implementation by Price and
Monaghan (2005). Optimal values of the damping parameter are found to be
{$\sigma$}=0.2-0.3 in 2D and {$\sigma$}=0.8-1.2 in 3D. With these parameters,
